column1: Between September 2017 and February 2018, how many people will be killed by sectarian actors in Nigeria?
column5: ['Less than 500', '500-750, inclusive', 'More than 750 but less than 1,000', '1,000 or more']
column6: ['Security and Conflict']
column11: Nigeria is facing increasing sectarian violence, even outside of violence attributed to Boko Haram (All Africa, Daily Post, Premium Times, IRIN). Outcome will be determined by the deaths attributed to "Sectarian Actor" on "Graph 2: Deaths by Perpetrator" on the Council on Foreign Relations Nigeria Security Tracker. The total for September through and February can be found by setting the start period at August 2017 and the end period at February 2018. Confused? Check our FAQ or ask us for help. Between September 2017 and February 2018, 618 deaths were attributed to sectarian actors. This question was closed as "b) 500-750, inclusive" with an end date of 28 February 2018. See our FAQ to learn about how we resolve questions and how scores are calculated.

column6: I received a response from CoFR about the Nigeria Security Tracker. I asked who is considered a "sectarian actor". They replied:
Currently 498 deaths. Almost at the end of this month, assuming there will be at least 2 more in the month of February, but I haven't heard of anything extreme happening yet this month there.
https://data.humdata.org/dataset/acled-data-for-nigeria
These data from CFR updates monthly, so it's a bit harder to 'guess' when the question closes before we see the data.

Depending upon which factions are being included in the Security Tracker's "sectarian actors", it could go over 750. Through December 2017, the Tracker has 356. There may be 294 from Fulani militias alone so far in 2018 (based on ACLED "actor 1"). That comes to 650 with a week more to go and presumably more militias to be included. If I include Bachama militias as "actor 1", the total for 2018 comes to 334. That raises the total so far to 690.

If the Nigeria Security Tracker is including Fulani Militias as "sectarian actors", it will go over 500 for the time period September 2017 through February 2018. According to ACLED, there have been 294 deaths with "actor 1" as Fulani ethnic militia so far in 2018 (not including Sept-Dec 2017).

Do they ever revise monthly totals upwards? Tracker strangely has January total at 55 Sectarian deaths but their raw data has the number at 201. If the January total of 55 holds, and the accurate cumulative total for September, October, November, December, and January is 356, then its a good bet the total is under 500. However, if the January tracker numbers are revised to match the raw data totals (from 55 to 201), then we're already past 500 fatalities. Unfortunately it is not clear how/when/or why the tracker numbers differ from the raw NST data. This is a bad question and should probably be withdrawn.

There have been a few of these "what score will be accumulated by the closing date" type of questions on GJO since I started about 5mth ago. The nice thing about this question is that it is the first I can recall where the publisher of the score that is being used to adjudicate the question (CFR in this case) also produces an interval update (the weekly updates) that appears to be concordant with the running total (the monthly updates). Tracking backwards for a few months, data recorded in the weekly updates (which always includes a specific date) sums to very closely approximate the monthly totals in the tracker, give or take only 1-2 deaths each month.

Sectarian violence has already killed about 350 people from September to the end of the year, so going over 500 seems likely. Sectarian violence is also the fastest growing portion of violence, so even as overall deaths slow, it seems likely that these deep-seated grudges will continue with like-for-like raids at slow but steady rates.

Well the average number of deaths per month in the last year has been 87, which is quite a bit lower than in years past. It is entirely possible that sectarian violence will pick up again in the next few months but I think we end up around 500 deaths, roughly the average for the last year.

Looking back in 6-month intervals (3/1 to 9/1, and 9/1 to 3/1 - you can manually type in the start and end dates instead of using the slide bars) to the start of the data (5/1/11), the average number of deaths by sectarian actors is 684 per 6-month period. The high mark came in 3/1-9/1/14, when 1,432 were killed. After this peak, deaths dropped by half, and have continued to decline to around the 500 mark.
